<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-10294] Variable&apos;s inferred type is upcasted to an Object</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-10294</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am not sure if this is a bug or a feature (or a general limitation of flow typing employed by Groovy).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have the following program&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;A {
  A foo() {
    def x = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; A()
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;) {
      x = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;
    }
    x
  }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Actualbehavior&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Actual behavior&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
org.codehaus.groovy.control.MultipleCompilationErrorsException: startup failed:
test.groovy: 7: [Static type checking] - Cannot &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; value of type java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt; on method returning type A
 @ line 7, column 5.
       x
       ^

1 error
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Expectedbehaviour&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Expected behaviour&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compile successfully&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tested against master&lt;/p&gt;</description>
